title: U.S. women's soccer team player didn't give Nazi salute | AP News
htmlTitle: U.S. women's soccer team player didn't give Nazi salute | AP News
snippet: Jul 16, 2019 ... CLAIM: Photo shows a member of the U.S. women's soccer team giving a Nazi salute in front of the Museum of Jewish Heritage in New York City.
htmlSnippet: Jul 16, 2019 ... CLAIM: Photo shows a member of the U.S. women's soccer team giving a Nazi salute in front of the Museum of Jewish Heritage in New York City.

metatags.og:description: CLAIM: Photo shows a member of the U.S. women’s soccer team giving a Nazi salute in front of the Museum of Jewish Heritage in New York City. AP’S ASSESSMENT: False. The photo shows soccer player Ashlyn Harris raising her hand in celebration next to her teammates, Allie Long and Megan Rapinoe, as they gathered outside the museum prior to a victory parade in New York City on July 10.
